==Old English==

===Etymology===
The original sense may have been a poetical comparison with a wild animal: it seems to be cognate with Old Norse ''bjǫrn'' ‘bear’, from Germanic ''*bernu-z''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /beoɹn/

===Noun===
'''beorn''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''beornas''')
# a [[man]], a [[warrior]]

